## Rules

1. Always use `--json` for structured output parsing.
2. Never use `iotcli setup` (interactive). Only non-interactive subcommands.
3. Never guess device names. Always run `iotcli --json list` first.
4. Always check device status before acting — it may be offline.
5. Validate the property name and value against the per-device table before calling `set`.
   For richer schemas (with enums, ranges, types) consult `iotcli.tools.json`.
